/f2012230-4c96-11ee-a7fb-74bf3b8d6ac7" style="height:837px;width:1718px;" alt="Duolingo will soon teach you to play music" data-uuid="1822a936-8b98-3608-bbbe-1fbfc4aaef68"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Duolingo</div></figure><p> Several screenshots show musical notation paired with piano keys (above), along with games like &quot;fill in the blanks&quot; and &quot;match the pairs.&quot; The app will appear alongside languages and math at the top of the main Duolingo screen. The math app is already available for iOS, with levels ranging from elementary to more advanced, all using interactive, gamified lessons.</p><p> A job posting spotted <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/duolingo-is-building-a-music-learning-app-065408671.html">earlier this year</a> provided hints that the company was working on a music app. Duolingo didn&#39;t give many details other than a few screenshots, but did say that &quot;the course is free, fun and effective. It plans to reveal the app fully at its <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.duolingo.com/duocon">Duocon conference</a> on October 11th. </p><div id="6ea8c69ae7024145b55164f32bbcfffb"><div style="max-width:56vh;"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:177.7778%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CnQr45XkkZE" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div></div></div> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/duolingo-will-soon-offer-gamified-music-lessons-120010824.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/duolingo-will-soon-offer-gamified-music-lessons-120010824.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4e805af7-5859-42c5-b602-83f11671d989</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightshol